definition: to translate and edit/translator-editor/(computing) to compile (source code)
to weave/to plait/to organize/to group/to arrange/to edit/to compile/to write/to compose/to fabricate

sentences.chinese: 設計了G代碼編譯運行環境。

sentences.english: A compilable example would be best.
sentences.chinese: 一個編譯例子是最好的。

sentences.english: You can compile code and run it in any scope or its default scope.
sentences.chinese: 您可以編譯代碼並且在任意範圍或默認範圍裏執行它。

sentences.english: The more methods compiled, the more memory the code occupies.
sentences.chinese: 編譯的方法越多，代碼佔用的內存就越多。

sentences.english: This new IR is more suited for implementation of traditional compiler optimizations.
sentences.chinese: 新IR更適合用來實現傳統編譯器優化。

sentences.english: Used C language to develop simple compiler.
sentences.chinese: 用C語言開發簡易編譯系統。

sentences.english: Once compiled, instructions are extracted and then reinserted in the original method body.
sentences.chinese: 編譯後，指令提取，然後重新插入原來的方法體。

sentences.english: The compiler treats the inline expansion options and keywords as suggestions.
sentences.chinese: 編譯器會將內嵌展開選項和關鍵字視同建議。

sentences.english: Your build system handles those declarations.
sentences.chinese: 編譯系統將會處理這些聲明。

sentences.english: This is a smart meter IC card , I have compiled can be used.
sentences.chinese: 這是一個IC卡智能水錶程序，我已編譯過可以用的。

sentences.english: Write a plugin in a C based language and compile it.
sentences.chinese: 基於C系語言編寫並且編譯插件。

sentences.english: Now as an aside, this may very well compile.
sentences.chinese: 此外，這個可以很好地編譯。

sentences.english: These require a header to be compiled in with the source under test.
sentences.chinese: 這些工具需要在測試中通過源編譯一個頭部。

sentences.english: Suppresses display of the copyright banner and informational messages during compilation.
sentences.chinese: 編譯過程中禁止顯示版權標誌和通知消息。

sentences.english: The compiler still has to allocate space for the empty class, right?
sentences.chinese: 編譯器仍然必須爲空類分配空間，對吧？

definition: variant of 匯編|汇编[hui4 bian1]
chief editor (of newspaper)/abbr. for 總編輯|总编辑

specially engaged/employed or commissioned for a special task
